^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|Now there is one other point regarding trump length.  In a competitive hand, it is almost never right to let the opponents play at the 2 level. Basically the rule applies through the 4 level for sure, after that, theoretically it still applies, but you must be more judicious.  And since 11+ card trump fits are pretty rare, I wouldn’t worry too much about it.|
