^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|yes david, you still must use judgment, but the law is a very good guideline. When in doubt, I find it works very well on most hands. Now let us go back to playing at the 2 level. In competitive hands, it is almost never right to let the opponents play at the 2 level.  So, if they stop at the 2 level, even if you only have an 8 card fit, you probably should usually go to the 3 level if you have to. However, once they get to the 3 level, you usually let them play it there unless you have a 9 card fit.|
